title: For Sale:  Smith & Wesson K-200
postcontent: For sale are these Smith & Wesson K-200 revolvers in 38 S&W caliber (not 38 Special). These are actually Military & Police Models of 1905 with change four that were chambered for the 38 S&W cartridge with a 200 grain bullet. The factory called it the 38/200 British Service Revolver and it was designed to fire the British service ammunition. The K-200's were built to commercial standards as the British Service Revolver during early 1940 till 1945 in the 38 S&W caliber. A normal 38 special round will only go about 3/4 of the way into the cylinder. These revolvers have 5 inch, pinned barrels, a six shot cylinder, fixed sights, case colored hammer and front serrated case hardened trigger. Both are marked "Made in U.S.A." on the forward right side plate with the standard size S&W Trade Mark in the larger rear area. Also stamped with flaming bomb and "U.S. Property G.H.D." on left side of top strap. They also have a "P" stamped on the left side frame just forward of the hammer. One weapon has been British Proofed with the appropriate stamps to include each cylinder. The second revolver has no country proof marks so it may not have made the trip overseas or to Canada like most did under the Lend-Lease Program. Both are in very good 85%+ condition with scattered finish wear. Both have the smooth grips with typical usage marks/dings and lanyard rings attached. Both bores are in excellent condition with good timing and lock-up. Serial number V584xxx has the British proofs and serial number V702xxx does not. $450 for individual purchase or will sell both for $800. No shipping.
